arage door opener actually wont open it.";i:11;s:88:"If I take my finger and loosen the weather shield all the way around the door will open.";i:12;s:86:"Let the paint cure well and then spray a little silicone on the area that is sticking.";i:13;s:81:"You should have a can of silicone around anyway to use on the garage door spring.";i:14;s:185:"When looking closely you could see little peaks and valleys on the door that fit perfectly into the valleys and peaks on the door jam like a puzzle exposing the previous color of paint.";i:15;s:90:"Every time the door opened the paint puzzle pieces made a sticking sound as they released.";i:16;s:140:"Closing and reopening the door shortly thereafter does not produce the same problem as the weather seal has had not had time to stick again.";i:17;s:42:"But many hours later sticky sticky sticky.";i:18;s:184:"The garage door tech explained that this results from latex paint which is partially on the back side of the weather stripping rubber that gets really tacky in the heat and direct sun.";i:19;s:72:"You will need the following items to repaint your sectional garage door.";i:20;s:47:"Paint can opener or a 5-in-1 tool A step stool.";i:21;s:30:"An old paintbrush for dusting.";i:22;s:27:"A stick for paint stirring.";i:23;s:21:"A 3-inch latex brush.";i:24;s:55:"Appropriate paint for the material of your garage door.";i:25;s:39:"Clean work bucket of 1 gallon capacity.";i:26;s:30:"Step by Step Repainting Guide.";i:27;s:98:"The paint may have cured in areas causing the door to get stuck and this could burn the motor out.";i:28;s:54:"Always allow each coat to dry before applying another.";i:29;s:71:"If you dont then the coats will never dry and your door will be sticky.";i:30;s:78:"Open the door and place a tarp on the ground partly inside and partly outside.";i:31;s:34:"This will make cleaning up easier.";i:32;s:117:"Acrylic latex paint is notorious for blocking or sticking to almost any surface it is in contact with while it cures."